headline: Goldman Sachs Doubles Down on These 2 Stocks
summary: With January nearly in the rearview mirror, Wall Street’s crystal-ball gazers are already sketching out what the rest of 2026 might look like. A few themes are coming into focus: the U.S. economy appears set to keep chugging along, with AI once again acting as a key engine of growth. The Federal Reserve has shifted into easing mode, although just how far rates will fall remains an open question. The bigger question is whether growth can remain stronger than many expect.
